templates.description: A shape that the player can control using the analog stick.

params.note: While the character is moving, continually rotate it so that it faces the same direction that it is moving.

The Character should slow to a stop when you stop controlling it, so it has the “Slow down” movement behavior. But when the analog stick is active we don’t want to be fighting against that effect, so it’s disabled temporarily.

templates.title: Character

templates.description: Triangular critter that chases the Character and flocks with other Creatures.

params.note: When this begins “chasing” the Character, play a sound and change colors. After five seconds, stop “chasing” and return to the normal color.
If this collides with the Character, switch to “chasing” it.
Every three seconds, flip a coin. On heads, check to see if the Creature is flocking. If it is, stop flocking. If it isn’t, start flocking. On tails, do nothing.

This rule decides where the Creature tries to go. If it is currently “chasing” the Character will prioritize that. If not, it will check if it is “flocking” with other Creatures and do that. If it is not chasing or flocking, it will wander.

templates.title: Creature

templates.description: Gem for the Character to collect, triggering a burst animation.

params.note: When the Character collides with this, play a sound, tell any Score counters to increment, and begin playing the disappear animation.
When the “disappear” animation finishes, destroy the Collectible.
